label: FGD211
info_overview: Remotely controlled Dimmer is designed to operate with or without neutral lead. It may be used as a switch in systems without neutral lead.
info_inclusion: The Dimmer enters the mode of inclusion after quick pressing three times the push-button connected to S1 terminal or push-button B located inside the housing.
info_exclusion: The Dimmer enters the mode of exclusion after quick pressing three times the push-button connected to S1 terminal or push-button B located inside the housing.
category_description: Any device attached to the wall that controls a binary status of something, for ex. a light switch

parameters.label: Separation of association sending (key 1)
parameters.description:
Activate/Deactivate association sending for group
				1 - Also see param #16

options.label: Map status to all devices in group 1
Map OFF status to group 1, memorize state
options.overview: Map OFF status to all devices in group 1, Double-clicking key sends 'turn on' command, dimmers memorize the last saved state (e.g. 50% brightness).

options.label: Map OFF status group 1, full brightness
options.overview: Commands are sent when device is turned off. Enabling device does not send control commands. Double-clicking key sends 'turn on' command and dimmers are set to 100% brightness.

parameters.label: Control key #2 behaviour
parameters.description: Key no.2 is not represented by any physical device
parameters.overview:
Key no.2 is not represented by any physical device - only devices in the association list.

parameters.label: Time of MANUALLY moving between dimming values
Time of AUTOMATIC moving between dimming values
parameters.overview: Options for changing parameter 1-255 (10ms - 2,5s) - 0: this value disables the smooth change in light intensity. NOTE: value 0 is required for inductive and capacitive devices unsuitable for dimming (e.g. fluorescent lamps, motors, etc...)

options.label: State NOT saved at power failure
options.overview: All outputs are set to OFF upon power restoration

options.label: State saved at power failure
options.overview: All outputs are set to previous state up

parameters.label: 3-way switch
parameters.overview: The function of 3-way switch provides the option to double key no. 1. The dimmer may control two bi-stable push-buttons or an infinite number of mono-stable push-buttons. (default value 0)

parameters.label: Synchronizing light level for associated devices
parameters.description: The dimmer communicate the level to the associated devices. (default value 0)

parameters.label: Change [On-Off] bi-stable keys
parameters.overview: This function allow user to change [On-Off] bi-stable keys (parameter no. 14) (default value 0)

options.label: Device changes status on key status change
Device status depends on key status
options.overview: Device status depends on key status: ON when the key is ON, OFF when the key is OFF.

parameters.label: Parm 20
parameters.overview:
This function will enable decreasing the minimum level of the Dimmer by extending the control impulse.[100 - 170]

By changing the minimem level, the user may completely dim LED bulbs.

Not all LED bulbs available on the market support this.

options.overview: ALARM FLASHING - relay will turn ON and OFF periodically (see param. 39)
